article.headline: Drake 59, Illinois State 55
article.story: DES MOINES, Iowa (AP) -- Quantel Murphy and Chaun Brooks scored 13 points each and Drake overcome a slow start to beat Illinois State 59-55 Wednesday night. Drake (7-6, 3-2 Missouri Valley) came from 10 points down in the first half, took control with a 15-0 second-half run and made eight of 10 free throws down the stretch to secure the victory. Lonnie Randolph added 11 points and six assists for Drake, which handed Illinois State (4-9, 0-5) its sixth straight loss. Najeeb Echols led the Redbirds with 12 points and Trey Guidry scored 11. Trailing 36-32 with 12:47 left, Drake made six of seven shots in scoring 15 straight points to take a 47-36 lead. Murphy started the burst with two straight layups and Randolph capped it with a floating 3-footer in the lane with 9:03 remaining. Illinois State drew to 56-54 on Guidry's three-point play with 1:14 to go, but Klayton Korver sank a free throw and Brooks made two to keep the Bulldogs on top. Drake shot only 17.4 percent in the first half and trailed 25-15 with 1:12 left. The Bulldogs cut the lead to 25-20 at halftime by making five free throws in the final 37 seconds -- two by Josh Powell and three by Brooks.
